[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man stabbed to death in Stroud named as Dennis Plater

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 82-year-old man who was stabbed to death in Stroud has been named as Dennis Plater.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gloucestershire Police launched a murder investigation after his body was found at an address on Walkley Hill on Friday.
In a statement, Mr Plater's family said he "was a beloved husband, father, brother and grandfather".
A 47-year-old man from Stroud was arrested in Southsea, Hampshire on Sunday and remains in custody.
